headline.main: VIENNA SIGNING DUE; Bulgarian Premier and Foreign Minister Go to City for Ceremony RIBBENTROP WILL ATTEND Italy and Japan Will Also Be Represented -- Blow to the Greeks Seen in Move Bulgaria Will Join the Axis Pact Today; Ceremony of Signing Slated for Vienna

lead_paragraph: BERLIN, Feb. 28 -- Bulgaria will become the seventh signatory of the Three-Power Pact in an official ceremony in Vienna some time over the week-end, but most probably tomorrow. As usual, however, no confirmation can be obtained in official German quarters tonight.
abstract: Swiss sources rept USSR influencing Bulgarian policy
